{"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"major":0,"minor":3},"abstract":[{"text":"This guide demonstrates the process for creating ","type":"text"},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"composite units"}]},{"text":". A composite unit is a unit category","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"that is created from other units.","type":"text"}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/documentation\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/CreatingCompositeUnits","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/guunitsgeneratorconversions\/creatingcompositeunits"]}],"sections":[],"kind":"article","hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/documentation\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions"]]},"metadata":{"title":"Creating Composite Units","modules":[{"name":"GUUnitsGeneratorConversions"}],"role":"article","roleHeading":"Article"},"seeAlsoSections":[{"title":"Essentials","identifiers":["doc:\/\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/documentation\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/GettingStarted","doc:\/\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/documentation\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/CreatingNewUnits","doc:\/\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/documentation\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/UsingCustomCodeGeneration","doc:\/\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/documentation\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/ConvertingBetweenCategories"],"generated":true}],"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"anchor":"Overview","type":"heading","text":"Overview","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A composite unit represents a unit category that contains other unit categories in it’s declaration. For example,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"consider a "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Velocity"}]},{"type":"text","text":" unit category. In this category, a velocity unit is represented as a distance divided by some time."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"This unit can thus be created by using the unit categories "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/documentation\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/DistanceUnits","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/documentation\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/TimeUnits","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" together, without specifying"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"new units."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"In this document, we will explore how to define the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Velocity"},{"text":" unit correctly using the protocols provided in this generator.","type":"text"}]},{"anchor":"Prerequisites","type":"heading","text":"Prerequisites","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Before following this guide, it is preferred that you read the ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"gettingstarted","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"creatingnewunits","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"and ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"usingcustomcodegeneration","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" guides. These guides will give an overview of the basic package structure","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"of this generator and how you can modify\/add swift files to create new units or language-specific implementations.","type":"text"}]},{"anchor":"The-Velocity-Unit","type":"heading","text":"The Velocity Unit","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Since we want to create a new Velocty unit, we must understand the existing units within this package. Velocity is made up of 2 units:","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Distance and Time. These units already exist in this package, but for simplicity I will place the code for these units below (see sections below).","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"We will want to combine these units into a Velocity unit performing a cartesian product between all cases between the two types. As such, we will"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"want to support units such as centimetres per millisecond (cm\/ms), millimetres per second (mm\/s) and metres per microsecond (m\/us) to name a few."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Every combination of Distance and Time must be represented by our new Velocity type."}]},{"anchor":"Distance","type":"heading","text":"Distance","level":3},{"code":["\/\/\/ A Unit for representing distances.","public enum DistanceUnits: String, UnitProtocol {","","    \/\/\/ Millimetres","    case millimetres","","    \/\/\/ Centimetres","    case centimetres","","    \/\/\/ Metres","    case metres","","    \/\/\/ The abbreviation of the unit.","    public var abbreviation: String {","        switch self {","        case .millimetres:","            return \"mm\"","        case .centimetres:","            return \"cm\"","        case .metres:","            return \"m\"","        }","    }","","    \/\/\/ The description of the unit.","    public var description: String {","        self.rawValue","    }","","}"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"anchor":"Time","type":"heading","text":"Time","level":3},{"code":["\/\/\/ A type for representing different time units.","public enum TimeUnits: String, UnitProtocol {","","    \/\/\/ Microseconds.","    case microseconds","","    \/\/\/ Milliseconds.","    case milliseconds","","    \/\/\/ Seconds","    case seconds","","    \/\/\/ The abbreviation of the time unit.","    public var abbreviation: String {","        switch self {","        case .microseconds:","            return \"us\"","        case .milliseconds:","            return \"ms\"","        case .seconds:","            return \"s\"","        }","    }","","    \/\/\/ The description of the time unit.","    public var description: String {","        self.rawValue","    }","","}"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"anchor":"The-CompositeUnit-Protocol","type":"heading","text":"The CompositeUnit Protocol","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"To start creating our Velocity unit, we must conform to the ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/documentation\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/CompositeUnit","type":"reference"},{"text":" protocol. Every ","type":"text"},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"composite unit","type":"text"}]},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"will conform to this protocol. The ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/documentation\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/CompositeUnit","type":"reference"},{"text":" protocol also conforms to the standard ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/documentation\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/UnitProtocol","type":"reference"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"meaning that every ","type":"text"},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"composite unit"}]},{"text":" is also a normal unit. We can start our Velocity unit by using a ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"struct"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"that conforms to this protocol.","type":"text"}]},{"code":["public struct Velocity: CompositeUnit {","","    \/\/ ToDo","","}"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"A ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/documentation\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/CompositeUnit"},{"text":" requires a ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"baseUnit"},{"text":" static property that represents the minimum-required relationship between","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the normal unit types within the composite unit. This relationship is defined through something called an ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/documentation\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/Operation"},{"text":".","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"An ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/documentation\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/Operation"},{"text":" is simply an abstract notation for defining mathematical relationships. The base unit of our Velocity","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"will be ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"metres per second","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":", or ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"DistanceUnits.metres"},{"text":" divided by ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"TimeUnits.seconds"},{"text":". We will use the following","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"code to represent this relationship using the ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/documentation\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/Operation"},{"text":" enumeration.","type":"text"}]},{"code":["\/\/\/ Defines a velocity unit with a base unit of metres per second.","public struct Velocity: CompositeUnit {","","    \/\/\/ The base unit (SI m\/s).","    public static let baseUnit: Operation = .division(","        lhs: .constant(declaration: AnyUnit(DistanceUnits.metres)),","        rhs: .constant(declaration: AnyUnit(TimeUnits.seconds))","    )","","}"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This code will not compile in it’s current state until we address a few more requirements in this type definition. For starters,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the Velocity unit has not finished providing all properties for the "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/documentation\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/CompositeUnit","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" conformance. We must add in a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"unit"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"property and an initialiser."}]},{"code":["\/\/\/ Defines a velocity unit with a base unit of metres per second.","public struct Velocity: CompositeUnit {","","    \/\/\/ The base unit (SI m\/s).","    public static let baseUnit: Operation = .division(","        lhs: .constant(declaration: AnyUnit(DistanceUnits.metres)),","        rhs: .constant(declaration: AnyUnit(TimeUnits.seconds))","    )","","    \/\/\/ A instance of this unit category.","    public let unit: Operation","","    \/\/\/ Initialise the Velocity from a derivation of the `baseUnit`.","    \/\/\/ - Parameter unit: The operation representing this unit. This parameter","    \/\/\/ must be a derivation of `baseUnit`. It cannot have a different structure.","    public init(unit: Operation) {","        self.unit = unit","    }","","}"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The Velocity code is now finished and ready to be compiled. For most composite units, this implementation is enough","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"to define a new composite unit. In some cases, the normal units within the composite unit may not conform to the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"protocols required to allow type-erasure using ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/documentation\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/AnyUnit","type":"reference"},{"text":". This is the case for this example, so we will now","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"examine how to change ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/documentation\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/DistanceUnits","type":"reference"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/documentation\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/TimeUnits","type":"reference"},{"text":" to meet this conformance.","type":"text"}]},{"anchor":"Making-Existing-Units-Convertible","type":"heading","text":"Making Existing Units Convertible","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To allow type-erase through the "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/documentation\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/AnyUnit","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" struct, we must conform "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/documentation\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/DistanceUnits","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/documentation\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/TimeUnits","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" to the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/documentation\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/UnitsConvertible","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" protocol. This protocol defines functions that generate an "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/documentation\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/Operation","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" for a conversion"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"between unit types within the same category. Both our "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/documentation\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/DistanceUnits","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/documentation\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/TimeUnits","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" use SI units in their"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"definition, therefore we can use an additional protocol to make this easy."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Since SI units use a prefixed base-10 notation in their unit derivations, we may use the protocol "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/documentation\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/Base10UnitsConvertible","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"instead of "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/documentation\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/UnitsConvertible","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" to achieve the conformance for type-erasure. This protocol will create the conversion"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"functions automatically for units that conform to it. The only thing we need to specify is the power of 10 each unit"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"is represented as. For example, millimetres is 10^-3 metres, and centimetres is 10^-2 metres. These powers of 10"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"will be represented inside a static dictionary property called exponents. Our distance and time types will thus"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"change to include the code below. Once we have provided this conformance, our code should now compile."}]},{"anchor":"Distance","type":"heading","text":"Distance","level":3},{"code":["\/\/\/ A Unit for representing distances.","public enum DistanceUnits: String, UnitProtocol, Base10UnitsConvertible {","","    \/\/\/ Millimetres","    case millimetres","","    \/\/\/ Centimetres","    case centimetres","","    \/\/\/ Metres","    case metres","","    \/\/\/ The exponents of the units expressed as base 10.","    public static let exponents: [DistanceUnits: Int] = [","        .millimetres: -3,","        .centimetres: -2,","        .metres: 0","    ]","","    \/\/\/ The abbreviation of the unit.","    public var abbreviation: String {","        switch self {","        case .millimetres:","            return \"mm\"","        case .centimetres:","            return \"cm\"","        case .metres:","            return \"m\"","        }","    }","","    \/\/\/ The description of the unit.","    public var description: String {","        self.rawValue","    }","","}"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"anchor":"Time","type":"heading","text":"Time","level":3},{"code":["\/\/\/ A type for representing different time units.","public enum TimeUnits: String, UnitProtocol, Base10UnitsConvertible {","","    \/\/\/ Microseconds.","    case microseconds","","    \/\/\/ Milliseconds.","    case milliseconds","","    \/\/\/ Seconds","    case seconds","","    \/\/\/ The exponents of the units expressed as base 10.","    public static let exponents: [TimeUnits: Int] = [","        .microseconds: -6,","        .milliseconds: -3,","        .seconds: 0","    ]","","    \/\/\/ The abbreviation of the time unit.","    public var abbreviation: String {","        switch self {","        case .microseconds:","            return \"us\"","        case .milliseconds:","            return \"ms\"","        case .seconds:","            return \"s\"","        }","    }","","    \/\/\/ The description of the time unit.","    public var description: String {","        self.rawValue","    }","","}"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"anchor":"Creating-the-C-Code","type":"heading","text":"Creating the C Code","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"At this point, we have correctly defined the Velocity unit category. We now have a choice on the best approach for"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"implementing the C code. The first option is to follow the previous guide for "},{"identifier":"usingcustomcodegeneration","isActive":true,"type":"reference","overridingTitleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Creating Custom Code Generation"}],"overridingTitle":"Creating Custom Code Generation"},{"type":"text","text":","},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the second is to conform Velocity to "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/documentation\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/UnitsConvertible","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" and use an existing "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/documentation\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/FunctionBodyCreator","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" for this purpose."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"We will demonstrate the "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/documentation\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/UnitsConvertible","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" approach."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"This approach is far simpler than all previous approaches thus far. You simply have to conform Velocty to ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/documentation\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/UnitsConvertible","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":".","type":"text"}]},{"code":["public extension Velocity: UnitsConvertible {}"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The default implementations of ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/documentation\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/UnitsConvertible","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" will create the conversion functions automatically since Velocity is a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/documentation\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/CompositeUnit","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":". You may also provide your own implementation by providing your own ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"conversion(to: ) -> Operation"},{"text":" function:","type":"text"}]},{"code":["public extension Velocity: UnitsConvertible {","","    func conversion(to unit: Velocity) -> Operation {","        \/\/ ToDo","    }","","}"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This is in no way required, but the option is open for types that may require it."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/documentation\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/FunctionBodyCreator","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" called "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/documentation\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/OperationalFunctionBodyCreator","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" is already provided for types that conform to "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/documentation\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/UnitsConvertible","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"You may use this type in the top module to generate the C code."}]},{"anchor":"Putting-it-all-Together","type":"heading","text":"Putting it all Together","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"We will now add all of the code into the top module for source code generation. The steps in this section are identical to the last steps"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"in "},{"overridingTitle":"Creating New Units","overridingTitleInlineContent":[{"text":"Creating New Units","type":"text"}],"type":"reference","identifier":"creatingnewunits","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"anchor":"Adding-the-Extension-to-UnitsGenerator","type":"heading","text":"Adding the Extension to UnitsGenerator","level":3},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You must still add the extensions onto the "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/documentation\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/UnitsGenerator","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"code":["\/\/\/ Velocity initialiser for C conversions.","extension UnitsGenerator where","    Creator == CompositeFunctionCreator<OperationalFunctionBodyCreator<Velocity>,","    CFunctionDefinitionCreator<Velocity>, NumericTypeConverter> {","","    \/\/\/ Initialise using Velocity and c conversions.","    public init() {","        self.init(creator: CompositeFunctionCreator(","            bodyCreator: OperationalFunctionBodyCreator(),","            definitionCreator: CFunctionDefinitionCreator(),","            numericConverter: NumericTypeConverter()","        ))","    }","","}"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"anchor":"Adding-the-C-Source-Generation-Code","type":"heading","text":"Adding the C Source Generation Code","level":3},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"You must change the ","type":"text"},{"code":"generateCFiles","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" function in ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/documentation\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/GUUnitsGenerator","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" to include the new C code. A type alias already exists to create","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"an ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/documentation\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/OperationalGenerator","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]},{"code":["public struct GUUnitsGenerator {","","    \/\/ ...","","    public func generateCFiles(in path: URL) throws {","        \/\/ ...","        let velocityGenerator = AnyGenerator(generating: Velocity.self, using: OperationalGenerator())","        let fileContents = HeaderCreator().generate(","            generators: [","                \/\/ ...","                velocityGenerator","            ]","        )","        .data(using: .utf8)","        \/\/ ...","        let cContents = CFileCreator().generate(","            generators: [","                \/\/ ...","                velocityGenerator","            ]","        )","        .data(using: .utf8)","        \/\/ ...","    }","","    \/\/ ...","","}",""],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"You must not forget to change ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"typeDefs"},{"text":" in ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/documentation\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/HeaderCreator","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" to include your new unit.","type":"text"}]},{"code":["public struct HeaderCreator {","","    \/\/ ...","","    private var typeDefs: String {","        let units: [(String, [CustomStringConvertible])] = [","            \/\/ ...","            (\"\/\/ Velocity Units.\", Array(Velocity.allCases))","        ]","        \/\/ ...","    }","","    \/\/ ...","","}"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"anchor":"C-Test-Generation","type":"heading","text":"C Test Generation","level":3},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"As our units work off a ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/documentation\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/Operation","isActive":true},{"text":", we may automatically generate the test code by inspecting the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"structure of the categories ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"baseUnit"},{"text":" property. This process is automatically handled by conforming to","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"a protocol called ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/documentation\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/OperationalTestable","isActive":true},{"text":" and using the ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/documentation\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/OperationalTestGenerator","isActive":true},{"text":".","type":"text"}]},{"code":["extension Velocity: OperationalTestable {","","    public static let testParameters: [ConversionMetaData<Velocity>: [TestParameters]] = defaultParameters","","}"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"You can see in the code above, that we have conformed to ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/documentation\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/OperationalTestable"},{"text":" by creating a static stored","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"property called ","type":"text"},{"code":"testParameters","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":". This property uses an underlying computed property called ","type":"text"},{"code":"defaultParameters","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"that is provided by ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/documentation\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/OperationalTestable"},{"text":" as part of it’s default implementation. Using this property","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"will create tests for a number of pre-defined values and edge cases. If you would like to add more custom","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"tests, then you may add then to ","type":"text"},{"code":"testParameters","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" yourself. The ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/documentation\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/ConversionMetaData"},{"text":" type simply stores","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the conversion information, i.e. the type converting from and the type converting to.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"We may now follow the same process for adding tests as normal units, but instead we may use the ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/documentation\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/OperationalTestGenerator","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":".","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Our test generation code in ","type":"text"},{"code":"GUUnitsGenerator.swift","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" will now contain the following lines for velocity:","type":"text"}]},{"code":["public struct GUUnitsGenerator {","","    \/\/ ...","","    public func generateCTests(in path: URL) {","        \/\/ ...","        let velocityGenerator = OperationalTestGenerator<Velocity>()","        let velocityFileCreator = TestFileCreator<OperationalTestGenerator<Velocity>>()","        createTestFiles(","            at: path,","            with: velocityFileCreator.tests(generator: velocityGenerator, imports: \"import CGUUnits\")","        )","        \/\/ ...","    }","","    \/\/ ...","","}",""],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"anchor":"Swift-Source-and-Test-Generation","type":"heading","text":"Swift Source and Test Generation","level":3},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Finally, we must follow a similar procedure to add the swift sources and tests."}]},{"code":["public struct GUUnitsGenerator {","","    \/\/ ...","","    public func generateSwiftFiles(in path: URL) {","        \/\/ ...","        writeFile(at: path, with: Velocity.category, and: swiftFileCreator.generate(for: Velocity.self))","        \/\/ ...","    }","","    \/\/\/ Generate files that test the swift layer of guunits.","    \/\/\/ - Parameter path: The folder containing the test files.","    public func generateSwiftTests(in path: URL) {","        \/\/ ...","        createTestFiles(at: path, with: swiftFileCreator.generate(with: OperationalTestGenerator<Velocity>()))","        \/\/ ...","    }","","    \/\/ ...","","}"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"}],"kind":"content"}],"references":{"doc://GUUnitsGeneratorConversions/documentation/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions/UnitsConvertible":{"role":"symbol","kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/GUUnitsGeneratorConversions\/doc